    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>&#8220;The top and bottom are white chocolate, onto which you sprinkle crushed peppermints, and the middle layer is a bittersweet ganache, ever so slightly soft and truffle-like, spiked with peppermint extract. It‚Äôs pretty, for one thing, but it‚Äôs also unusually delicious: heady with mint, only moderately sweet, and surprisingly sophisticated, crunchy in parts and smooth in others, like a proper chocolate confection. It‚Äôs Americana, yes, but Americana in a vintage designer dress. If the butter cookies I made last week bore a faint resemblance to my grandmother, this peppermint bark is my fantasy great-aunt: the one who lives in San Francisco, wears Jackie O. dresses and glasses with vermilion frames, makes hot chocolate from scratch, and always knows what‚Äôs showing at SFMOMA. What a lady she would be. I wish she actually existed. At least I have peppermint bark.&#8221;</></>You could sell ice to the eskimos, in a heartbeat&#8230; oh me, oh my!!</p>
    </div>

